[{"id":"FT557189","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"Which of the following diagrams best illustrates how a displacement in an ionic crystal results in cleavage and brittleness?","choicesHtml":["<table class=\"table\">\n\t<tbody>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td><u>Before Displacement</u> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<u>After Displacement</u></td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t<img alt=\"The structure on the left shows sixteen circles in four rows and four columns. The circles touch each other. Each circle contains either a plus sign or a minus sign, and the signs alternate so each circle touches only circles with the opposite sign. The structure on the right shows the same sixteen circles, but the third and fourth columns are moved down a distance equal to one diameter, making three circles in the second column adjacent to circles with the same sign in the third column.\" height=\"122\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/media.academicmerit.com/110c328bf9075f9b78217fb9eadd2ad7/original.png\" width=\"377\"></td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t</tbody>\n</table>","<table class=\"table\">\n\t<tbody>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td><u>Before Displacement</u> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<u>After Displacement</u></td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t<img alt=\"The structure on the left shows twenty large circles in four rows and five columns. The large circles do not touch each other, and each one contains a minus sign. In each of the spaces surrounded by four large circles is a small circle that contains a plus sign. The structure on the right is identical to the structure on the left except that one of the small circles is missing and one of the small circles has a 2 before the positive sign.\" height=\"124\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/media.academicmerit.com/02cbe9a75b3e554aa94e68f193f14573/original.png\" width=\"424\"></td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t</tbody>\n</table>","<table class=\"table\">\n\t<tbody>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td><u>Before Displacement</u> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<u>After Displacement</u></td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t<img alt=\"The structure on the left shows sixteen large circles in four rows and four columns. The large circles do not touch each other, and each one contains a plus sign. Small circles, each labeled electron, are scattered in the spaces between the large circles. The structure on the right shows the same large circles and small circles labeled the same way, but the third and fourth columns of large circles are moved down a distance equal to one half of their diameter. The electrons are scattered in different positions than in the diagram on the left\" height=\"141\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/media.academicmerit.com/1472debe98aecbc1b33ab3ab519591f3/original.png\" width=\"423\"></td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t</tbody>\n</table>","<table class=\"table\">\n\t<tbody>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td><u>Before Displacement</u> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<u>After Displacement</u></td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t<img alt=\"The structure on the left shows three straight rows of large circles . The large circles in each row touch each other, but they do not touch the circles in other rows. Each large circle is connected to two small circles, except for the ones at the ends, which are each connected to three small circles. The structure on the right is identical to the one on the left I except that the rows are not straight, they form waves.\" height=\"135\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/media.academicmerit.com/d8ce672fd4313ecd7f5960ed6c318621/original.png\" width=\"525\"></td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t</tbody>\n</table>"],"answer":-1}]